The paper discusses the use of deep convolutional neural networks for predicting material properties from microstructure images, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the need for a sustained research effort, which suggests a materials science (cs.MS) sub-category. The use of generative deep learning models for material design space exploration and property optimization falls under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
